menuconfig SAMPLES_KOTLIN
	bool "Kotlin samples"
	depends on KOTLIN
	help
	  You can build sample Kotlin/Native kernel code here.

	  These samples demonstrate how to write Linux kernel modules
	  in Kotlin/Native, using the Kotlin kernel API to interact
	  with kernel subsystems.

	  If unsure, say N.

if SAMPLES_KOTLIN

config SAMPLE_KOTLIN_MINIMAL
	tristate "Minimal"
	help
	  This option builds the Kotlin/Native minimal module sample.

	  It demonstrates the basic structure of a Kotlin kernel module:
	  module declaration via annotations, initialization, and cleanup.

	  To compile this as a module, choose M here:
	  the module will be called kotlin_minimal.

	  If unsure, say N.

config SAMPLE_KOTLIN_USERSPACE
	tristate "Kotlin Userspace Init (linux-kotlin kernel)"
	help
	  This option builds a pure native Kotlin executable and configures
	  an initramfs specification for it.

	  When booted with this initramfs, the Linux kernel will start the
	  Kotlin process as PID 1 (init), running entirely without bash,
	  glibc, or a JVM!

	  If unsure, say N.

config SAMPLE_KOTLIN_PRINT
	tristate "Printing macros"
	help
	  This option builds the Kotlin/Native printing sample module.

	  It demonstrates the various kernel logging functions available
	  from Kotlin: pr_info, pr_warn, pr_err, pr_debug, etc.

	  To compile this as a module, choose M here:
	  the module will be called kotlin_print.

	  If unsure, say N.

config SAMPLE_KOTLIN_PARAMETERS
	tristate "Module parameters"
	help
	  This option builds a Kotlin/Native module that demonstrates
	  how to declare and use module parameters (the equivalent of
	  C's module_param() macro).

	  To compile this as a module, choose M here:
	  the module will be called kotlin_parameters.

	  If unsure, say N.

config SAMPLE_KOTLIN_DRIVER_PLATFORM
	tristate "Platform Driver"
	help
	  This option builds a Kotlin/Native platform driver sample.

	  To compile this as a module, choose M here:
	  the module will be called kotlin_driver_platform.

	  If unsure, say N.

config SAMPLE_KOTLIN_PCI_DRIVER
	tristate "PCI driver"
	depends on PCI
	help
	  This option builds a sample Kotlin/Native PCI driver.
	  It demonstrates probing and registering a PCI device natively
	  using Kotlin and C-interop.

	  If unsure, say N.

endif # SAMPLES_KOTLIN
